🧠 OS Concept 1: Belady’s Anomaly

Very famous trap question.

1️⃣ Strange Idea

Normally:

More memory pages should reduce page faults.

Right?

Seems obvious.

But sometimes…

❌ More frames can increase page faults.

That is:

👉 Belady’s Anomaly

Happens in:

FIFO page replacement.

(Not generally in LRU)

🧠 Analogy

Adding more shelves but becoming less organized.

More space, worse performance.

Strange but possible.

🎯 Placement Trap

Q: Which algorithm shows Belady’s anomaly?

👉 FIFO

🧠 Memory Trick
Belady = more memory, more faults (weird!)
🧠 OS Concept 2: Demand Paging
1️⃣ Simple Idea

Load page only when needed.

Not before.

Instead of loading whole process:
Load only required pages
Why Good?

✔ Saves memory
✔ Faster startup

Page Fault

If page absent:

👉 page fault occurs
OS loads it from disk.

🔗 Connection

Virtual memory heavily uses:

👉 demand paging

🎯 Placement Question

Q: What triggers demand paging?

👉 Page fault.

🧠 Memory Trick
Demand paging = load on demand
⚙️ COA Concept 3: Cache Miss Types

🔥 Very common.

1️⃣ Compulsory Miss

First time access.

Can’t avoid.

Example

First ever access to block.

Miss unavoidable.

2️⃣ Conflict Miss

Because blocks compete for same cache location.

Common in direct mapped cache.

3️⃣ Capacity Miss

Cache too small.

Needed data evicted.

🧠 Memory Trick
Compulsory = first time
Conflict = mapping clash
Capacity = cache too small
🎯 Placement Question

Q: Which miss reduced by set associative cache?

👉 Conflict miss.

⚙️ COA Concept 4: Superscalar vs Superpipeline

Classic confusion question.

Superscalar

Multiple instructions per cycle.

2+ instructions in same cycle
Superpipeline

Break pipeline into more smaller stages.

Increase overlap.

Analogy

Superscalar:

More workers.

Superpipeline:

More assembly stations.

Difference
Superscalar	Superpipeline
more instructions/cycle	deeper pipeline
multiple units	more stages
🎯 Placement Trap

Q: Difference?

👉 Superscalar increases width.
👉 Superpipeline increases depth.

🧠 Memory Trick
Scalar = wider
Pipeline = deeper
